&gt;I&#39;ve been placed in charge of learning the concepts of JUnit and 
&gt;reporting them back to our team.  I&#39;ve reviewed many of the messages 
&gt;in this archive and in the extreme progrogramming group archive.  I 
&gt;haven&#39;t been able to find any Testing Standards besides those 
&gt;compiled in the &quot;JUnit Best Practices&quot; article.  Are there any 
&gt;standards for validation or any general standards that anyone has 
&gt;incorporated in their own projects?  The thought behind this is by 
&gt;alligning everyone into some basic testing standards we can document 
&gt;the process and use it as a requirements doc.

Testing standards are specific to every team that does testing. Your team
probably should write up recommendations (or &quot;standards&quot;), but your team&#39;s
requirements would be different than another team.

Extreme Programming states that you should ask yourself &quot;what could possibly
go wrong&quot; when you are writing code test-first. If you are writing satellite
software, and are concerned that gamma rays will corrupt memory, then your
definition of &quot;possibly go wrong&quot; are different from someone writing a
simple game.


